<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n15038e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15038e">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15038e"> 38(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> d. ap. Asiatics / <font face="wake">C</font> European / Rome &amp; her / pinnion &frasl; / Amer. &amp; Eng.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; poi, conosciuta la Spagna, la dissero <i>Esperia ultima</i>, la quale cos&igrave; rest&ograve; detta. Alla stessa fatta la prima <mark>Europa dovette essere essa Grecia a riguardo dell&apos; Asia</mark>: cos&igrave; la prima Jonia dovette essere questa parte di Grecia occidentale, di cui ci &egrave; pur restata detto il mare Jonio: e l&apos;Asia, che or si dice Minore, dovette essere la Jonia Seconda, parte occidentale di Grecia a riguardo dell&apos; Asia maggiore, che rest&ograve; detta Asia assolutamente. Onde si fa verisimile che i Greci avessero prima conosciuto l&apos;Italia che l&apos;Asia, e che Pittagora da questa Jonia occidentale vi avesse tragittato. <br><font color="green">[Then, after they came to know of Spain, it became <i>Esperia ultima</i> [&lsquo;furthest Hesperia&rsquo;]</font>, a name that it also retained. In the same way, the first <mark>Europe must have been Greece relative to Asia</mark>, the first Ionia must have been the part of western Greece that is still called &lsquo;the Ionian Sea&rsquo;, and the Asia that is now called &lsquo;Asia Minor&rsquo; must have been the second lonia, the western part of Greece, relative to Greater Asia, which has survived as &lsquo;Asia&rsquo; without qualification. Hence it becomes probable that the Greeks knew of Italy before they knew Asia, and that Pythagoras crossed to Italy from western Ionia.] <small> Giovanni Battista Vico, <a name="VICO2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#VICO2"><cite title="source">Principes de la philosophe de l'histoire</cite></a> (edition unknown) ?Book II, Ch. LX</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15214e" href="c15all.htm#c15214e">VI.C.15:214(e)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
